<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>88355</id>
    <title>Merging cells deletes comments</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">(Split from bug 56279)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Merging Calc cells doesn't offer any option to retain comments other than those in the first of the cell range.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Steps to reproduce</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">1 Open the attached sample spreadsheet</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">2 Separately merge the highlighted ranges A4:B4 and B6:C6</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">(The choice "Should the contents of the hidden cells be moved into the first cell?" is offered, but makes no difference)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Expected results</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">- Both comments are retained</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Actual results</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">- Only the comment for B6:C6 is retained</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">(The question then arises of what to do if more than one cell has a comment.</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">Possibly just merge them into one comment?)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
